&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Length of each train = 160 metres&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken to cross each other = 32 seconds&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both trains are running in opposite directions with the same speed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative Speed = (Total Distance) / Time&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of each train = Relative Speed / 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total Distance = 160 + 160 = 320 metres&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative Speed = 320 / 32&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative Speed = 10 m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of each train = 10 / 2 = 5 m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Convert m/s to km/h:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of each train = 5 &amp;times; 18/5 = 18 km/h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The speed of each train is 18 km/h.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;70 pens and 130 pencils&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Greatest Common Divisor (GCD)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GCD of 70 and 130&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Factors of 70: 1, 2, 5, 7, 10, 14, 35, 70&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Factors of 130: 1, 2, 5, 10, 13, 26, 65, 130&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Common factors: 1, 2, 5, 10&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; GCD = 10&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of boxes for pens = 70 &amp;divide; 10 = 7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of boxes for pencils = 130 &amp;divide; 10 = 13&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total number of boxes = 7 + 13 = 20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The correct answer is option (3).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Notebook marked price (N&lt;sub&gt;MP&lt;/sub&gt;) = ₹35&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Notebook discount (N&lt;sub&gt;D&lt;/sub&gt;) = 20%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pen marked price (P&lt;sub&gt;MP&lt;/sub&gt;) = ₹100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pen discount (P&lt;sub&gt;D&lt;/sub&gt;) = 79%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings on an item = Marked Price &amp;times; Discount&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings on notebook = ₹35 &amp;times; 20% = 35 &amp;times; 0.20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Savings on notebook = ₹7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings on pen = ₹100 &amp;times; 79% = 100 &amp;times; 0.79&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Savings on pen = ₹79&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total savings = Savings on notebook + Savings on pen&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Total savings = ₹7 + ₹79&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Total savings = ₹86&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The correct answer is option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
